Preconditions:
The arrays `nums1` and `nums2` are not null.
The lengths of `nums1` and `nums2` are equal.
The elements in `nums1` and `nums2` are integers.

Postconditions:
The method returns an integer value.
The returned value is the minimum absolute sum difference after replacing at most one element in the array `nums1`.
The returned value is modulo `10^9 + 7`.